     3→## 🎯 KISS - Keep It Simple, Stupid!
     4→
     5→### The 3-Question Rule
     6→Before writing ANY code, ask:
     7→1. **Can I use what already exists?** → DO THAT
     8→2. **Can I solve this with a simple method?** → DO THAT
     9→3. **Do I really need this abstraction NOW?** → PROBABLY NOT
    10→
    11→## 📊 SIMPLICITY DECISION MATRIX
    12→
    13→| Scenario | Simple Solution | Over-Engineered Solution |
    14→|----------|----------------|-------------------------|
    15→| Validate email format | `email.matches("^.+@.+\\..+$")` | EmailValidatorFactoryBuilder |
    16→| Transform list | `list.stream().map(...).toList()` | Custom TransformationStrategy |
    17→| Single if/else | Direct if statement | Strategy pattern |
    18→| 3 similar methods | Extract common code | Abstract base class + 3 subclasses |
    19→| Configuration values | `@Value` annotation | Complex ConfigurationManager |
    20→| Simple CRUD | Spring Data Repository | Custom DAO pattern |
    21→
    22→## 🚫 ANTI-PATTERNS: DON'T DO THIS!
    23→
    24→### 1. Factory Madness
    25→```java
    26→// ❌ OVER-ENGINEERED - 5 files for a simple creation
    27→public interface OrderFactory {
    28→    Order createOrder(OrderType type);
    29→}
    30→
    31→public class OrderFactoryImpl implements OrderFactory {
    32→    private final Map<OrderType, OrderCreator> creators;
    33→    // ... 50 lines of factory setup
    34→}
    35→
    36→public interface OrderCreator {
    37→    Order create();
    38→}
    39→
    40→public class StandardOrderCreator implements OrderCreator {
    41→    // ... implementation
    42→}
    43→
    44→// ✅ SIMPLE - One method that works
    45→public class OrderService {
    46→    public Order createOrder(final OrderType type, final OrderRequest request) {
    47→        return switch (type) {
    48→            case STANDARD -> new Order(request, calculateStandardShipping());
    49→            case EXPRESS -> new Order(request, calculateExpressShipping());
    50→            case BULK -> new Order(request, calculateBulkDiscount());
    51→        };
    52→    }
    53→}
    54→```
    55→
    56→### 2. Abstraction Addiction
    57→```java
